text: Hey jeong, thanks for responding. No worries everyone is busy. And that's great news. As long as it works that's what matters. Oh fx that's interesting.

Studio tour? What studio was this that's really good and very handy. When it comes to shows tracking and object. It's more interesting to track shake shots or an action  shot with an object to track for object tracking plus you will get to understand how to problem solve more as well.

3DEqualizer is the top for matchmove it helps a lot in different areas and the tools are really useful for varies of shots. I'd highly recommend it. It's good to stick to one and learn all about it but at the same time you will be able to demonstrate what you need and want from a shot.

The first link you sent looks good but there seems to be some sliding going on with the globe, a good thing to know with shiny object it's harder because its reflective. So the point you track might struggle to stay in one spot.
And the second video doeant work? Did you remove it?

Focus on one and get very good at it. Terms of numbers of shots maybe 4 to five really good shots. But they would each need to be something complex and will have to give you a new way of how to approach. :)
My favourite one you have is tracking 03 although it's only moving forward. It's nice but the motion isnt doing anything else.
